questions.question:
What will be the output of the following code? Show step-by-step execution:

String s1 = "Java";
String s2 = s1.concat(" Programming");
System.out.println(s1);
System.out.println(s2);
System.out.println(s1 == s2);

Trace the output of the following code and determine the final content of sb and str:

StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder("Hello");
sb.append(" World");
sb.insert(5, ",");
sb.replace(6, 11, "Java");
sb.reverse();
String str = sb.toString();
System.out.println(str);

Given the following code, what is the initial capacity and final length of the StringBuilder after all operations?

StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
sb.append("university");
sb.append(" Advanced Java");
sb.append(" Semester 6");
sb.append(" Module 2");
System.out.println(sb.length());
System.out.println(sb.capacity());

What will be printed by the following code?

String str = " Welcome to Java Programming ";
String s1 = str.trim();
String s2 = str.strip();
String s3 = str.stripLeading();
String s4 = str.stripTrailing();
System.out.println("[" + s1 + "]");
System.out.println("[" + s2 + "]");
System.out.println("[" + s3 + "]");
System.out.println("[" + s4 + "]");
